sentences.en: She was in continuous employment until the age of sixty-five.
sentences.cn: 她连续不断地受雇于人，一直工作到六十五岁。

sentences.en: Sixty-five percent of the 1987 budget went for nuclear weapons research and production.
sentences.cn: 1987年预算的65%用在了核武器的研制上。

sentences.en: The flooding, caused by three days of torrential rain, is the worst in sixty-five years.
sentences.cn: 由3天暴雨引发的这场洪水泛滥是65年来最为严重的。
